The Legend of Zelda Navi's Quest 1.8 for AmigaOS 68k (http://www.zeldaroth.fr/) by the French Team

Authors:
--------
concept / code: Vincent Jouillat
Illustration: Solene Jouillat,  Adrien Baptis
AmigaOS 68k port by Artur 'Arti' Jarosik

Requirements:
-------------
 minimal:
An Amiga with RTG or AGA, AHI, 68060 CPU and 40MB of RAM

 recommended:
An Amiga with V2 accelerator 
V4 Standalone
Should work on MorphOS

 optional:
CD32 compatible gamepad (7 button)

PORT NOTES:
- Added Triple buffer
- Rewrote audio code to use XM modules, 16bit up to 44kHz (depending on AHI settings)
- Tested on Amiga 500 with V2 500 and V4 Stand-alone on AmigaOS 3.9
- press 'V' to disable/enable Vsync
- AGA version included

Gamepad controls:
Use the sword: Green
Great technique: hold Green to load, release when the tune's end to use the spin attack. 
Move Navi: Forward (Right trigger) held + keyboard arrows 
Use selected object: Yellow (only if the selected object is usable) 
Lift an item: Backward (Left trigger) (hit again to throw it) 
View map: Blue (after you found the map) 
Open a chest/Read/Speak: Forward (Right trigger) 
Select/Confirm/Pass: Red 
Access/Quit the selection item menu: Red 
Save/Quit: Play/Pause 

